about.summary: Algorithms for accelerating the convergence of slow, monotone sequences from smooth, contraction mapping such as the EM and MM algorithms. It can be used to accelerate any smooth, linearly convergent acceleration scheme.  A tutorial style introduction to this package is available in a vignette on the CRAN download page or, when the package is loaded in an R session, with vignette("turboEM").

name: r-turboem
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '2018.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-turboem
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: turboEM_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/turboEM_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/turboEM/turboEM_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 46d965a9477212e89f39979d6d7abc1aec2ef3ea9dde9831751611db9ba857f6

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1001
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-doparallel
    - r-foreach
    - r-iterators
    - r-numderiv
    - r-quantreg
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-doparallel
    - r-foreach
    - r-iterators
    - r-numderiv
    - r-quantreg

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('turboEM')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('turboEM')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://www.jhsph.edu/agingandhealth/People/Faculty_personal_pages/Varadhan.html
  license: GPL-2
  summary: Algorithms for accelerating the convergence of slow, monotone sequences from smooth,
    contraction mapping such as the EM and MM algorithms. It can be used to accelerate
    any smooth, linearly convergent acceleration scheme.  A tutorial style introduction
    to this package is available in a vignette on the CRAN download page or, when the
    package is loaded in an R session, with vignette("turboEM").
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
